main event: An unidentified object shaped like a horseshoe, described as a vapor trail in the shape of a question mark, was observed in Warner Robins, Georgia on January 15, 1967.
interesting points: The object had a reddish hue and was approximately ten feet in length.,Witnesses described the object appearing stationary before it gradually faded with daylight.,A Nike-Hercules rocket launch was correlated with the sighting due to a cloud release to study upper winds.,Descriptions of the object included it oscillating or pulsating at several points on its surface.,Reports of similar sightings were noted, causing intrigue about the object's proximity to a power plant which experienced a power failure.
sighted object: a vapor trail shaped like a horseshoe and question mark
witness description: A civilian who observed the object described it as moving rapidly and erratically, while blinking off and on.
